0needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20younger%20children%2C%20I'd%20choose%20the%20Pilot's%20roomy%2C%20easy-to-use%2C%20and%20durable%20cabin.%20But%20as%20they%20and%20I%20grow%20older%2C%20count%20me%20in%20on%20the%20Palisade's%20refined%2C%20isolating%20ride%20and%20heated%20massaging%20seats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhonda-pilot-vs-hyundai-palisade-review-family-suv-compared-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734257642000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6758b553dc8b666017f26588%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhonda-pilot-vs-hyundai-palisade-review-family-suv-compared-2024-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22I%20drove%20the%20Honda%20Pilot%20Elite%20and%20Hyundai%20Palisade%20Calligraphy%20three-row%20family%20SUVs%20to%20compare%20their%20capabilities.%20It%20was%20a%20tie%20with%20important%20distinctions.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bzhang%40businessinsider.com%20(Benjamin%20Zhang)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhonda-pilot-vs-hyundai-palisade-review-family-suv-compared-2024-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22You%20might%20want%20to%20have%20your%20next%20job%20interview%20in%20the%20morning%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20women%20in%20a%20job%20interview%20reviewing%20resume%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663e573c9686a6f37bfe9c48%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EScheduling%20a%20job%20interview%20in%20the%20morning%20could%20be%20a%20smart%20strategy.%3Cp%3EOlga%20Rolenko%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMorning%20interviews%20may%20yield%20higher%20scores%20due%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbias-against-older-and-younger-workers-bad-for-business-2024-10%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einterviewer%20bias%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20research%20shows.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBias%20in%20hiring%20can%20be%20influenced%20by%20the%20time%20of%20day%2C%20affecting%20candidate%20evaluations.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAI%20tools%20could%20reduce%20this%2C%20offering%20fairer%20assessments%20than%20manual%20methods.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20get%20to%20choose%20when%20to%20schedule%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwent-through-a-dozen-interviews-didnt-get-the-job-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejob%20interview%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20you%20might%20want%20to%20grab%20a%20coffee%20and%20go%20for%20a%20morning%20slot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20some%20people%20conducting%20interviews%20tend%20to%20give%20higher%20scores%20to%20candidates%20they%20meet%20with%20earlier%20in%20the%20day%20compared%20with%20the%20afternoon%2C%20a%20startup's%20review%20of%20thousands%20of%20interviews%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20an%20absolute%2C%20of%20course%2C%20and%20candidates%20can%20still%20kill%20it%20well%20after%20lunchtime.%20Yet%2C%20in%20a%20job%20market%20where%20employers%20in%20fields%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fentry-level-jobs-tech-roles-require-years-of-experience-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etech%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffinding-job-awful-right-now-drop-in-openings-tough-search-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eslow%20to%20hire%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20even%20a%20modest%20advantage%20could%20make%20a%20difference%2C%20Shiran%20Danoch%2C%20an%20organizational%20psychologist%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSpecific%20interviewers%20have%20a%20consistent%20tendency%20to%20be%20harsher%20or%20more%20lenient%20in%20their%20scores%20depending%20on%20the%20time%20of%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20possible%20that%20in%20the%20morning%2C%20interviewers%20haven't%20yet%20been%20beaten%20down%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhumblebragging-about-busy-work-calendar-can-hurt-productivity-morale-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eback-to-back%20meetings%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20or%20are%20perhaps%20still%20enjoying%20their%20own%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcoffee-cup-test-fears-about-rise-of-ai-hiring-process-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efirst%20coffee%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDanoch%20and%20her%20team%20noticed%20the%20morning-afternoon%20discrepancy%20while%20reviewing%20datasets%20on%20thousands%20of%20job%20interviews.%20Danoch%20is%20the%20CEO%20and%20founder%20of%20Informed%20Decisions%2C%20an%20artificial%20intelligence%20startup%20focused%20on%20helping%20organizations%20reduce%20bias%20and%20improve%20their%20interviewing%20processes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20the%20inferences%20on%20the%20time-of-day%20bias%20are%20drawn%20from%20the%20datasets%20of%20interviewers%20who%20use%20Informed%20Decisions%20tools%20to%20score%20candidates.%20The%20data%20reflected%20those%20who've%20done%20at%20least%2020%20interviews%20using%20the%20company's%20system.%20Danoch%20said%20that%20in%20her%20company's%20review%20of%20candidates'%20scores%2C%20those%20interviewed%20in%20the%20morning%20often%20get%20statistically%20significant%20higher%20marks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20good%20news%2C%20she%20said%2C%20is%20that%20when%20interviewers%20are%20made%20aware%20that%20they%20might%20be%20more%20harsh%20in%20the%20afternoon%2C%20they%20often%20take%20steps%20to%20counteract%20that%20tendency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20many%20cases%2C%20happily%2C%20we're%20actually%20seeing%20that%20the%20feedback%20that%20we're%20providing%20helps%20to%20reduce%20the%20bias%20and%20eventually%20eliminate%20the%20bias%2C%26quot%3B%20Danoch%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20she%20said%2C%20interviewers%20often%20don't%20get%20feedback%20about%20their%20hiring%20practices%2C%20even%20though%20finding%20the%20right%20talent%20is%20%26quot%3Bsuch%20a%20crucial%20part%26quot%3B%20of%20what%20hiring%20managers%20and%20recruiters%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20other%20researchers%20have%20identified%20how%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feuropepmc.org%2Farticle%2FMED%2F32000532%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etime%20of%20day%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20whether%20someone%20might%20be%20a%20morning%20person%20or%20an%20evening%20person%20%E2%80%94%20can%20affect%20decision-making%20processes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20examination%20of%20more%20than%201%2C000%20parole%20decisions%20in%20Israel%20found%20that%20judges%20were%20likelier%20to%20show%20leniency%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20day%20and%20after%20breaks.%20However%2C%20that%20favorability%20decreased%20as%20judges%20made%20more%20decisions%2C%20according%20to%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmailsuite.com%2Fl%2Ff33c9b8588f75b67b75309785dfb0d95b4a3ac11%3Fw%3DdHBhcmFkaXNAYnVzaW5lc3NpbnNpZGVyLmNvbQ%26url%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.pnas.org%252Fdoi%252F10.1073%252Fpnas.1018033108%26u%3D2210619%26signature%3Dc042ea69b161e438%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2011%20research%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b99aa422-e3b9-4404-921d-1230a7eea7d0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETech%20could%20help%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20possible%20that%20if%20tools%20like%20artificial%20intelligence%20take%20on%20more%20responsibility%20for%20hiring%2C%20job%20seekers%20won't%20have%20to%20worry%20about%20the%20time%20of%20day%20they%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20all%20of%20the%20concerns%20about%20biases%20in%20AI%2C%20partiality%20involved%20in%20more%20%26quot%3Bmanual%26quot%3B%20hiring%20where%20interviewers%20ask%20open-ended%20questions%20often%20leads%20to%20more%20bias%20than%20does%20AI%2C%20said%20Kiki%20Leutner%2C%20cofounder%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FSeeTalent.ai%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESeeTalent.ai%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20startup%20creating%20tests%20run%20by%20AI%20to%20simulate%20tasks%20associated%20with%20a%20job.%20She%20has%20researched%20AI%20ethics%20and%20that%20of%20assessments%20in%20general.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeutner%20told%20BI%20that%20it's%20likely%20that%20in%20a%20video%20interview%20conducted%20by%20AI%2C%20for%20example%2C%20a%20candidate%20might%20have%20a%20fairer%20shot%20at%20landing%20a%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20just%20have%20people%20do%20unstructured%20interviews%2C%20ask%20whatever%20questions%2C%20make%20whatever%20decisions%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20because%20everything%20is%20recorded%2C%20Leutner%20said%2C%20there%20is%20documentation%20of%20what%20decisions%20were%20made%20and%20on%20what%20basis.%20Ultimately%2C%20she%20said%2C%20it's%20then%20possible%20to%20take%20that%20information%20and%20correct%20algorithms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAny%20structured%20process%20is%20better%20in%20recruitment%20than%20not%20structuring%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Leutner%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2228b1785b-d2f3-43a3-97a7-586a68fdc43f%5C%22%3EHumans%20are%20'hopelessly%20biased'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEric%20Mosley%2C%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Workhuman%2C%20which%20makes%20tools%20for%20recognizing%20employee%20achievements%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20data%20created%20by%20humans%20will%20be%20biased%20%E2%80%94%20because%20humans%20are%20%26quot%3Bhopelessly%20biased.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20pointed%20to%202016%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fnews%2Fwonk%2Fwp%2F2016%2F09%2F07%2Fafter-a-favorite-football-team-loses-judges-punish-black-defendants-more%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20indicating%20that%20juvenile%20court%20judges%20in%20Louisiana%20doled%20out%20tougher%20punishments%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0particularly%20to%20Black%20youths%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0after%20the%20Louisiana%20State%20University%20football%20team%20suffered%20a%20surprise%20defeat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMosley%20said%2C%20however%2C%20that%20AI%20can%20be%20trained%20to%20ignore%20certain%20biases%20and%20look%20for%20others%20to%20eliminate%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETaking%20that%20approach%20can%20help%20humans%20guard%20against%20some%20of%20their%20natural%20tendencies.%20To%20get%20it%20right%2C%20however%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20have%20safeguards%20around%20the%20use%20of%20AI%2C%20he%20said.%20These%20might%20include%20ethics%20teams%20with%20representatives%20from%20legal%20departments%20and%20HR%20to%20focus%20on%20issues%20of%20data%20hygiene%20and%20algorithm%20hygiene.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20taking%20those%20precautions%20and%20solely%20relying%20on%20AI%20can%20even%20risk%20scaling%20humans'%20biases%2C%20Mosley%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20basically%20just%20unleash%20it%20in%20a%20very%20simplistic%20way%2C%20it'll%20just%20replicate%20them.%20But%20if%20you%20go%20in%20knowing%20that%20these%20biases%20exist%2C%20then%20you%20can%20get%20through%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDanoch%2C%20from%20Informed%20Decisions%2C%20said%20that%20if%20people%20conducting%20interviews%20suspect%20they%20might%20be%20less%20forgiving%20after%20the%20morning%20has%20passed%2C%20they%20can%20take%20steps%20to%20counteract%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBefore%20you%20interview%20in%20the%20afternoons%2C%20take%20a%20little%20bit%20longer%20to%20prepare%2C%20have%20a%20cup%20of%20coffee%2C%20refresh%20yourself%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-interview-success-morning-bias-search-strategy-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A173425758