20got%20together.%20We%20weren't%20in%20that%20category.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wondered%20what%20an%20open%20marriage%20would%20feel%20like.%20I%20viewed%20myself%20as%20an%20open-minded%20person%2C%20but%20I%20had%20a%20hunch%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpoly-vee-polyamorous-marriage-how-it-works-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehusband's%20nonmonogamy%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20be%20too%20painful%20for%20me.%20Could%20I%20handle%20him%20going%20on%20vacation%20without%20me%3F%20Not%20coming%20home%20at%20night%3F%20I%20was%20doubtful.%20We%20decided%20to%20play%20it%20by%20ear.%20We'd%20see%20how%20things%20progressed%20and%20then%20reassess.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20really%2C%20nothing%20progressed.%20We%20worked%2C%20we%20took%20care%20of%20the%20kids%2C%20and%20we%20continued%20to%20live%20as%20we%20had%20before%2C%20he%20told%20me%2C%20as%20though%20nothing%20had%20changed.%20But%20everything%20had%20changed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlmost%20exactly%20one%20year%20later%2C%20it%20became%20clear%20that%20clinging%20to%20the%20status%20quo%20would%20not%20work.%20I%20knew%20I%20had%20two%20choices%2C%20and%20both%20were%20excruciating%3A%20stay%20with%20my%20husband%20knowing%20I%20would%20always%20have%20to%20share%20him%2C%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frebuilding-my-life-after-painful-divorce-middle-age-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eend%20my%20marriage%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20be%20alone.%20If%20I%20left%2C%20my%20new%20world%20might%20be%20bleak%20and%20lonely%2C%20but%20at%20least%20it%20would%20hold%20the%20possibility%20of%20some%20future%20joy.%20At%2035%2C%20I%20was%20still%20young.%20I%20wanted%20to%20find%20a%20relationship%20where%20I%20would%20feel%20like%20enough.%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20compete%20with%20someone%20else.%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20the%20only%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20both%20came%20to%20this%20realization%20simultaneously.%20We%20sat%20together%20on%20the%20couch%20one%20dismal%20night.%20We%20didn't%20even%20have%20to%20say%20anything.%20I%20realized%20I%20could%20not%20flourish%20in%20this%20union%2C%20and%20he%20realized%20he%20could%20not%20live%20his%20life%20fully%20with%20me%20by%20his%20side.%20We%20held%20each%20other%20and%20cried.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2232b30678-76fa-493e-8452-c0cfeeb9523a%5C%22%3EOur%20separation%20was%20slow%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20the%20last%20week%20we%20lived%20together%20before%20he%20moved%20out.%20There%20should%20be%20a%20name%20for%20this%20strange%20period.%20A%20Divorceymoon%2C%20maybe.%20A%20time%20when%20instead%20of%20starting%20to%20build%20your%20life%20together%2C%20you%20must%20begin%20to%20take%20it%20apart.%20Separating%20the%20books%2C%20photos%2C%20and%20posters%20was%20the%20easy%20part.%20Far%20harder%20was%20cutting%20up%20the%20fabric%20of%20our%20shared%20life.%20Soon%2C%20I%20would%20stop%20seeing%20him%20when%20he%20came%20home%20from%20work.%20Soon%2C%20I%20would%20wake%20up%20alone%20in%20the%20morning.%20Soon%2C%20the%20marriage%20would%20be%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20few%20weeks%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdetermined-marriage-end-in-divorce-backfired-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estarting%20a%20life%20apart%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20more%20painful%20than%20I%20expected.%20The%20house%20was%20so%20quiet%20when%20the%20kids%20were%20with%20him%2C%20and%20I%20was%20always%20happy%20when%20they%20came%20back.%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20had%20not%20understood%20true%20loneliness%20until%20then.%20To%20have%20a%20full%20family%20one%20day%2C%20and%20the%20next%20day%2C%20to%20be%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20separation%20continued%20at%20a%20gradual%20pace.%20We%20still%20spent%20time%20together%20as%20a%20family%2C%20going%20out%20to%20eat%20or%20to%20the%20playground%20with%20the%20kids.%20We%20went%20camping%20on%20the%20Cape.%20Once%2C%20we%20even%20traveled%20to%20Spain%20together.%20And%20then%2C%20a%20few%20months%20later%2C%20he%20met%20someone.%20Soon%20we%20were%20spending%20less%20time%20with%20each%20other%2C%20and%20I%20missed%20him%20terribly.%20But%20then%2C%20a%20few%20months%20after%20that%2C%20I%20met%20someone%20too.%20We%20had%20now%20become%20two%20separate%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fc507d06-2673-4fc8-a2c4-afa20cbecabf%5C%22%3EWe've%20incorporated%20our%20new%20big%20loves%20into%20our%20big%20family%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYears%20passed%2C%20and%20relationships%20came%20and%20went%20for%20both%20of%20us.%20We%20rarely%20met%20each%20other's%20love%20interests.%20They%20rarely%20joined%20us%20at%20our%20shared%20meals.%20They%20didn't%20feel%20like%20part%20of%20the%20joint%20family%20we%20still%20had%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20then%20my%20ex%20met%20his%20big%20love.%20And%20two%20years%20later%2C%20so%20did%20I.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20guess%20it%20shouldn't%20have%20surprised%20me%20that%20I%20liked%20my%20ex's%20new%20boyfriend%20and%20that%20he%20liked%20mine%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20the%20two%20boyfriends%20liked%20each%20other.%20We%20all%20seemed%20to%20have%20the%20same%20sense%20of%20humor%20and%20spent%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20laughing%2C%20and%20often%20had%20dinner%20at%20each%20other's%20houses.%20Usually%2C%20I'm%20not%20a%20big%20fan%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdinks-childfree-couples-friends-millennial-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esocializing%20with%20other%20couples%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20often%20feels%20unbalanced%20because%20I%20rarely%20like%20both%20spouses.%20But%20this%20didn't%20feel%20like%20that.%20This%20felt%20like%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20now%20been%20more%20than%2020%20years%20that%20the%20four%20of%20us%20have%20been%20hanging%20out%20together%2C%20sometimes%20every%20week%3B%20sometimes%20more.%20Recently%20our%20gatherings%20have%20gotten%20much%20larger.%20I've%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstepmom-experience-didnt-want-kids-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epicked%20up%20a%20stepdaughter%3C%2Fa%3E%20along%20the%20way%2C%20so%20now%20we%20are%20often%20joined%20by%20our%20three%20daughters%2C%20three%20of%20their%20spouses%2C%20and%20three%20little%20grandkids.%20Last%20year%20I%20had%20to%20buy%20a%20bigger%20table%20and%20four%20sets%20of%20benches.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20days%2C%20the%20grandkids%20hold%20center%20stage%20at%20the%20table.%20Once%20the%20food%20is%20cleared%2C%20we'll%20play%20a%20round%20of%20Junior%20Mad%20Libs%20which%20will%20make%20everyone%20shriek%20with%20laughter.%20Then%20later%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20my%20ex%20will%20pull%20out%20their%20guitars%20and%20everyone%20will%20join%20in%20for%20a%20raucous%20round%20of%20Wheels%20on%20the%20Bus.%20Though%20there's%20not%20a%20specific%20name%20for%20what%20we%20are%20to%20each%20other%2C%20the%20way%20there%20are%20for%20relationships%20like%20%26quot%3Bdaughter-in-law%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Buncle%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20term%20%26quot%3Bfamily%26quot%3B%20still%20fits%20%E2%80%94%20perhaps%20even%20better%20than%20it%20did%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdivorced-after-husband-came-out-new-family-dynamics-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734257221000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6759920b52dd0818d1a65f36%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdivorced-after-husband-came-out-new-family-dynamics-2024-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22My%20husband%20and%20I%20divorced%20when%20he%20came%20out%20to%20me.%20We%20both%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20new%20people%20and%20spend%20time%20together%20as%20a%20new%20kind%20of%20family.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Sarena%20Neyman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.busines