%20their%20financial%20regrets%20with%20BI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMany%20said%20they%20had%20made%20mistakes%20that%20led%20them%20to%20return%20to%20work%20after%20retirement.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThis%20is%20part%20of%20an%20ongoing%20series%20about%20older%20Americans'%20regrets.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20retiring%20less%20than%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20Sylvia%2C%2064%2C%20is%20back%20at%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20under%20%242%2C000%20a%20month%20she%20receives%20in%20Social%20Security%20isn't%20enough%20to%20pay%20her%20bills%2C%20and%20she%20has%20little%20retirement%20savings%2C%20so%20she%20recently%20started%20a%20job%20as%20a%20cashier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESylvia%20is%20one%20of%20many%20older%20adults%20who%20have%20shared%20their%20retirement%20stories%20with%20Business%20Insider%20in%20recent%20months.%20Some%20said%20they%20returned%20to%20work%20out%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-savings-social-security-baby-boomers-without-savings-401k-poverty-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinancial%20necessity%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20others%20unretired%20to%20stay%20active%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomers-living-social-security-government-aid-snap-loneliness-crisis-isolation-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecombat%20loneliness%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They're%20among%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emore%20than%202%2C000%20Americans%20who%20have%20responded%20to%20a%20reader%20survey%20about%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Folder-americans-regret-retirement-savings-taking-social-security-early-investments-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elife%20regrets%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20story%20is%20part%20of%20an%20ongoing%20series.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESylvia%2C%20who%20requested%20to%20use%20only%20her%20first%20name%20for%20privacy%2C%20was%20hoping%20to%20land%20a%20part-time%20role%20in%20education%20or%20local%20government%20near%20Albany%2C%20New%20York.%20Though%20she%20has%20decades%20of%20experience%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eand%20has%20submitted%20hundreds%20of%20applications%2C%20she's%20had%20no%20luck%20getting%20hired%20in%20her%20field%20and%20opted%20to%20pick%20up%20shifts%20at%20the%20grocery%20store.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20Sylvia%20isn't%20sure%20whether%20she%20will%20ever%20be%20able%20to%20stop%20working.%20She%20said%20she's%20%26quot%3Bmad%26quot%3B%20at%20herself%20for%20not%20building%20a%20strong%20financial%20foundation%20for%20retirement%20%E2%80%94%20she%20thought%20Social%20Security%20would%20be%20enough%20to%20get%20by.%20The%20manual%20labor%20of%20a%20grocery%20job%20is%20taking%20a%20toll%20on%20her%20mind%20and%20body%2C%20but%20she%20said%20she%20needs%20the%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20scanning%20groceries%20and%20I'm%20thinking%3A%20'I%20hold%20a%20master's%20degree%2C%20I%20recently%20received%20an%20award%20from%20one%20of%20our%20state%20senators%2C%20and%20I%20can't%20obtain%20professional%20work%2C'%26quot%3B%20Sylvia%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BCan%20you%20believe%20that%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EWe%20want%20to%20hear%20from%20you.%20Are%20you%20an%20older%20American%20with%20any%20life%20regrets%20you'd%20be%20comfortable%20sharing%20with%20a%20reporter%3F%20Please%20fill%20out%20this%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fforms%2Fd%2Fe%2F1FAIpQLScB-4a6dV6jak2g6t-CoOdxFIENDSZggxHVbvsz6ry4dGoUjg%2Fviewform%3Fusp%3Dsf_link%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Equick%20form%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bd6dbe6c-f6d5-4313-97e4-17f57904fb9a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESome%20older%20adults%20can't%20retire%20because%20of%20their%20finances%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESylvia's%20experience%20isn't%20uncommon.%20The%20Federal%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20St.%20Louis%20found%20that%202.4%20million%20excess%20retirements%20occurred%20in%20the%20US%20as%20the%20pandemic%20began%20in%202020%2C%20meaning%20the%20number%20of%20retirees%20far%20surpassed%20the%20Fed's%20prediction.%20However%2C%20an%20Indeed%20Hiring%20Lab%20analysis%20of%20individual-level%20Census%20data%20found%20that%201.5%20million%20retirees%20had%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.troweprice.com%2Fpersonal-investing%2Fresources%2Finsights%2Funretiring-why-recent-retirees-want-to-go-back-to-work.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereturned%20to%20the%20workforce%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20March%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20study%20published%20in%20May%2C%20the%20wealth%20management%20firm%20T.%20Rowe%20Price%20estimated%20that%2048%25%20of%20those%20working%20in%20retirement%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eneeded%20their%20paycheck%2C%20while%2045%25%20chose%20to%20work%20for%20social%20and%20emotional%20benefits.%20The%20study%20was%20based%20on%20survey%20responses%20of%202%2C895%20401(k)%20plan%20participants%20and%201%2C136%20retirees%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20more%2C%20one%20in%20five%20adults%20ages%2050%20and%20over%20surveyed%20by%20AARP%20and%20the%20University%20of%20Chicago's%20NORC%20research%20firm%20in%20January%20said%20they%20didn't%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-x-baby-boomers-savings-cant-afford-retirement-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretirement%20savings%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20going%20back%20to%20work%20as%20an%20older%20American%20isn't%20so%20simple.%20These%20job%20seekers%20may%20struggle%20to%20land%20a%20job%20because%20of%20ageism%20in%20the%20hiring%20process%2C%20said%20Jessica%20Johnston%2C%20the%20senior%20director%20for%20the%20National%20Council%20on%20Aging's%20Center%20for%20Economic%20Well-Being.%20They%20could%20also%20face%20difficulty%20finding%20a%20job%20because%20their%20skills%20don't%20meet%20changing%20technology%20requirements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20people%20who%20are%20trying%20to%20reenter%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20them%20need%20job%20training%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20the%20amount%20of%20digital%20literacy%20required%20to%20do%20a%20lot%20of%20even%20part-time%20work%20is%20not%20inconsequential.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20retirees%20who%20return%20to%20the%20workforce%20for%20financial%20reasons%20are%20also%20conscious%20that%20earning%20%3Cem%3Etoo%20much%3C%2Fem%3E%20can%20cost%20them%20more%20in%20lost%20benefits%20than%20they%20make%20in%20take-home%20pay.%20Government%20assistance%20programs%20that%20some%20older%20Americans%20rely%20on%2C%20like%20Medicaid%20or%20SNAP%2C%20have%20income%20ceilings.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EFor%20example%2C%20a%20single%20person%20in%20Utah%2C%20like%20Claudia%20Rufino%2C%20must%20keep%20her%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Egross%20monthly%20income%20below%20%241%2C670%20to%20qualify%20for%20Medicaid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERufino%20feels%20trapped%20in%20that%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecatch-22.%20As%20a%20single%20mom%2C%20she%20worked%20multiple%20jobs%20in%20retail%20and%20design%20to%20support%20her%20family%2C%20but%20a%20tight%20budget%20meant%20she%20couldn't%20build%20savings.%20After%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eretiring%20and%20taking%20Social%20Security%20a%20decade%20ago%20%E2%80%94%20which%20currently%20amounts%20to%20%241%2C103%20a%20month%20%E2%80%94%20the%2072-year-old%20said%20she%20had%20been%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Estruggling%20to%20afford%20essentials.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20help%20cover%20her%20bills%2C%20Rufino%20took%20a%20part-time%20role%20working%20with%20foster%20children%20near%20her%20home%20in%20Salt%20Lake%20City.%20She%20said%20that%20she%20earns%20a%20stipend%20of%20a%20few%20hundred%20dollars%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERufino%20wishes%20she%20had%20extra%20money%20to%20travel%20in%20her%20golden%20years%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20want%20to%20go%20see%20the%20world%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20have%20the%20money%20to%20do%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20would%20pursue%20a%20higher-paying%20job%2C%20but%20she%20said%20that%20would%20risk%20her%20Medicaid%20benefits%2C%20meaning%20she%20would%20have%20to%20pay%20more%20of%20her%20healthcare%20costs%20out-of-pocket.%20She%20also%20lives%20in%20a%20subsidized%20housing%20unit%2C%20and%20she%20said%20a%20higher%20income%20would%20mean%20an%20untenable%20rent%20increase.%20Those%20are%20trade-offs%20she%20can't%20afford%20to%20make.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGoing%20back%20to%20work%20is%20not%20worth%20it%20for%20me%20in%20my%20situation%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20make%20enough%20money%20to%20make%20it%20worthwhile.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2231433a0d-7947-441c-9798-03e23d8dd643%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EResources%20for%20older%20adults%20in%20the%20job%20market%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERetirement%20and%20economy%20experts%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Etold%20BI%20that%20there%20are%20resources%20for%20older%20adults%20who%20are%20back%20on%20a%20job%20hunt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohnston%20said%20that%2C%20for%20those%20who%20can't%20find%20work%2C%20government%20assistance%20programs%20can%20help%20some%20Americans%20afford%20essentials%20like%20groceries%2C%20housing%2C%20healthcare%2C%20and%20transportation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20August%2C%20the%20National%20Council%20on%20Aging%20estimated%20that%209%20million%20adults%20ages%2065%20and%20older%20would%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncoa.org%2Farticle%2Fnine-million-older-adults-are-not-getting-benefits-they-are-eligible-for%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equalify%20for%20SNAP%20benefits%3C%2Fa%3E%20but%20weren't%20enrolled%2C%20with%20many%20of%20those%20people%20eligible%20for%20other%20programs%20as%20well%2C%20like%20Social%20Security%20and%20Medicare%20Savings.%20The%20group%20hypothesized%20that%20some%20lower-income%20older%20adults%20don't%20know%20they%20are%20eligible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohnston%20said%20lower-income%20older%20Americans%20should%20take%20the%20food%2C%20healthcare%2C%20transportation%2C%20and%20housing%20benefits%20they%20are%20entitled%20to%20%E2%80%94%20local%20senior%20centers%20and%20benefits%20counselors%20can%20help%20them%20get%20started%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20a%20big%20believer%20that%20you%20can't%20budget%20your%20way%20out%20of%20poverty%2C%26quot%3B%20Johnston%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllison%20Shrivastava%2C%20an%20economist%20for%20the%20job-search%20platform%20Indeed%2C%20added%20that%20older%20adults%20looking%20to%20return%20to%20work%20should%20lean%20on%20their%20professional%20networks%20to%20get%20a%20leg%20up%20on%20open%20positions%20and%20interviews.%20She%20also%20advised%20that%20job%20seekers%20spend%20time%20obtaining%20updated%20certifications%20and%20technology%20skills%20in%20their%20field%3A%20%26quot%3BIt%20shows%20that%20you%20are%20willing%20to%20learn%20and%20you're%20willing%20to%20adapt%2C%26quot%3B%20Shrivastava%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20financial%20need%20isn't%20the%20only%20reason%20that%20retirees%20return%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBonnie%20Cote%2C%2075%2C%20returned%20to%20the%20workforce%20part%20time%20as%20a%20substitute%20teacher%20shortly%20after%20retiring%20about%2010%20years%20ago.%20She%20spent%20decades%20working%20for%20the%20Department%20of%20Education%20near%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20along%20with%20a%20stint%20teaching%20art%20at%20a%20nearby%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECote's%20income%20supplements%20her%20savings%20and%20%242%2C300%20monthly%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ESocial%20Security%20checks%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebut%20she%20says%20her%20job%20keeps%20her%20active.%20She%20loves%20teaching%2C%20being%20social%2C%20and%20working%20with%20students%20on%20assignments%20and%20art%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECote%20said%20she%20felt%20pressured%20by%20friends%20and%20financial%20advisors%20to%20leave%20her%20career%20in%20education%20in%20her%20mid-60s%20and%20came%20to%20regret%20it.%20She%20said%20she%20retired%20too%20soon%2C%20and%20she's%20happiest%20in%20a%20classroom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%20matter%20what%20age%20you%20are%2C%26quot%3B%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ECote%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20should%20be%20able%20to%20get%20a%20job.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20you%20unretired%3F%20Are%20you%20struggling%20with%20finances%20in%20retirement%3F%20If%20you're%20open%20to%20sharing%20your%20story%20with%20a%20reporter%2C%20reach%20out%20to%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aallisonkelly%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eallisonkelly%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Folder-americans-unretiring-regret-not-saving-retirement-social-security-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734256921000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F675329b58fbb2783ed304748%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Folder-americans-unretiring-regret-not-saving-retirement-social-security-2024-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Some%20older%20Americans%20are%20unretiring%20because%20of%20financial%20challenges.%20This%20story%20is%20part%20of%20BI's%20ongoing%20series%20on%20retirement%20regrets.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22allisonkelly%40businessinsider.com%20(Allie%20Kelly)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Folder-americans-unretiring-regret-not-saving-retirement-social-security-2024-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Rohit%20Sharma%20faces%20flak%20for%20unimagi