0in%20true%20fintech%20fashion%20has%20been%20rendered%20into%20a%20key%20metric%20that%20is%20tracked%20each%20quarter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20recent%20blog%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmax.levch.in%2Fpost%2F765636918645080064%2Fto-build-a-meritocracy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epost%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Levchin%20defined%20the%20term%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20culture%20of%20individuals%20doing%20productive%20work%20for%20the%20company%20in%20the%20most%20efficient%20way%20possible%20and%20helping%20others%20do%20the%20same%2C%20while%20generally%20having%20a%20good%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20puzzle%2C%20Levchin%20said%2C%20is%20how%20do%20companies%20actually%20accomplish%20this%20%E2%80%94%20and%20what%20should%20they%20avoid%20doing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20high-performance%20culture%20is%20never%20final%2C%20Linford%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BThat%20is%20a%20function%20of%20sustained%20focus%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20now%2C%20one%20approach%20Linford%20said%20he's%20focused%20on%20is%20less%20about%20maximizing%20day-to-day%20work%20experiences%20and%20more%20about%20creating%20additional%20opportunities%20to%20connect%20in%20person%2C%20especially%20in%20cities%20like%20Austin%2C%20Texas%2C%20where%20he%20and%20about%2040%20other%20employees%20live.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20just%20take%20a%20couple%20of%20days%20a%20quarter%20and%20get%20a%20WeWork%2C%20and%20folks%20can%20come%20together%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20point%20isn't%20that%20these%20folks%20are%20working%20together.%20They're%20not.%20They%20literally%20have%20no%20work%20overlap.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20point%20wasn't%20that.%20It%20was%20to%20be%20Affirmers%20together%20in%20a%20room%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20where%20culture%20gets%20reinforced.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBringing%20together%20people%20from%20across%20the%20company%20%E2%80%94%20like%20an%20Android%20engineer%2C%20a%20recruiter%2C%20an%20HR%20team%20member%2C%20and%20the%20COO%20%E2%80%94%20underscores%20a%20value%20expressed%20by%20Levchin%20that%20Affirm%20is%20made%20up%20of%20individuals%20working%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20such%20cross-functional%20coworking%20likely%20helps%20the%20company%20avoid%20the%20pitfall%20of%20an%20%26quot%3Bus%20vs%20them%26quot%3B%20dynamic%20that%20Levchin%20says%20is%20prohibited%20at%20Affirm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMax%20felt%20compelled%2C%20I%20think%2C%20to%20write%20that%20because%20we%20do%20want%20to%20%3Cem%3Enot%3C%2Fem%3E%20let%20culture%20just%20get%20created%2C%26quot%3B%20Linford%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20we're%20influencing%20what%20it%20is%20the%20team%20is%20feeling%2C%20thinking%2C%20et%20cetera%2C%20and%20leave%20our%20mark%20on%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20Affirm%2C%20Spotify%20is%20another%20major%20company%20that%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspotify-remote-work-policy-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecommitted%20to%20not%20calling%20staff%20back%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20office.%20While%20Amazon%2C%20Meta%2C%20Apple%2C%20and%20Google%20have%20all%20ordered%20staff%20back%20to%20the%20office%20for%20either%20a%20hybrid%20or%20fully%20in-person%20setup%2C%20Spotify%20has%20said%20it%20will%20continue%20to%20have%20physical%20offices%20and%20a%20%26quot%3Bcore%20week%26quot%3B%20where%20teams%20are%20encouraged%20to%20meet%20up%20in%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20music-streaming%20platform%20said%20the%20flexible%20policy%20led%20to%20a%20decrease%20in%20attrition%20rates%2C%20increased%20workplace%20diversity%2C%20and%20hiring%20times%20that%20were%20six%20days%20faster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Spotify's%20chief%20human%20resources%20officer%2C%20Katarina%20Berg%2C%20said%20in%20an%20October%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.raconteur.net%2Ftalent-culture%2Fspotify-chro-office-return-layoffs-hr-role%5C%22%20t