0(often%20unruly)%20tourists%20and%20displace%20locals.%20Barcelona%2C%20which%20has%20an%20estimated%2020%2C000%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsold-airbnb-property-selling-lessons-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAirbnb%20listings%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20has%20said%20it%20will%20ban%20all%20short-term%20rentals%20by%202028.%20M%C3%A1laga%20will%20stop%20giving%20out%20new%20short-term-rental%20permits%20in%20dozens%20of%20neighborhoods.%20New%20York%20enacted%20a%20law%20in%202023%20that%20wiped%20nearly%20all%20short-term%20rentals%20off%20the%20map.%20Other%20cities%2C%20like%20London%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frich-americans-buying-old-french-chateaus-mansions-problems-costs-maintenence-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EParis%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20have%20been%20enforcing%20strict%20limits%20on%20the%20number%20of%20nights%20each%20year%20that%20a%20property%20can%20be%20listed%20for%20short-term%20renting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Airbnb%2C%20terra%20incognita%20looks%20more%20appealing%20as%20some%20of%20its%20terra%20firma%20becomes%20less%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Airbnb%20was%20new%20and%20growing%20rapidly%20in%20the%202010s%2C%20there%20was%20little%20regulation%20on%20short-term%20rentals.%20Many%20did%20not%20anticipate%20how%20homeowners%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-new-side-hustle-getting-rich-airbnb-super-hosts-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eeven%20renters%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20would%20turn%20Airbnb%20into%20overnight%20miniature%20business%20empires.%20But%20complaints%20mounted%20over%20the%20years.%20Residents%20reported%20that%20short-term%20renters%20often%20had%20parties%20that%20brought%20trash%2C%20noise%2C%20and%20general%20chaos%20to%20buildings%20and%20neighborhoods%2C%20even%20after%20the%20company%20barred%20guests%20from%20hosting%20large%20gatherings.%20Locals%20also%20blamed%20the%20lucrative%20rentals%20for%20pushing%20up%20housing%20prices.%20Housing%20costs%20are%20influenced%20by%20many%20factors%2C%20but%20in%202020%2C%20researchers%20found%20that%20Airbnb%20growth%20in%20the%20median%20ZIP%20code%20accounted%20for%20an%20increase%20of%20%249%20in%20monthly%20rent%20and%20%241%2C800%20in%20home%20prices%2C%20making%20up%20one-fifth%20of%20rent%20growth%20and%20one-seventh%20of%20property%20value%20increases.%20A%20report%20by%20the%20New%20York%20City%20comptroller%20found%20that%20between%202009%20and%202016%2C%209.2%25%20of%20the%20jump%20in%20rental%20rates%20could%20be%20tied%20to%20Airbnb.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20this%20point%2C%20dozens%20of%20local%20governments%20around%20the%20world%20have%20enacted%20laws%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairbnb-numbers-shrink-hotel-prices-soar-ban-nyc-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eregulating%20short-term%20rentals%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20are%20bespoke%20to%20their%20cities.%20This%20gives%20places%20where%20Airbnb%20is%20looking%20to%20expand%20the%20advantage%20of%20seeing%20how%20various%20regulations%20have%20started%20to%20affect%20housing%20availability%20elsewhere%2C%20should%20they%20want%20to%20move%20proactively.%20%26quot%3BEven%20though%20those%20places%20that%20Airbnb%20could%20be%20pushing%20into%20may%20not%20have%20a%20%5Bregulatory%5D%20framework%2C%20there's%20at%20least%20these%20examples%20where%20governments%20have%20recognized%20the%20need%20to%20protect%20housing%20and%20implemented%20successful%20ways%20of%20regulating%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Murray%20Cox%2C%20founder%20of%20Inside%20Airbnb%2C%20which%20scrapes%20Airbnb%20data%20to%20show%20its%20footprint%20in%20cities%20around%20the%20world.%20Cities%20could%20take%20approaches%20from%20other%20playbooks%2C%20such%20as%20requiring%20Airbnb%20to%20share%20data%20with%20local%20officials%2C%20zoning%20short-term%20rentals%20to%20more%20commercial%20neighborhoods%2C%20or%20allowing%20hosts%20to%20rent%20out%20primary%20residences%20a%20limited%20number%20of%20nights%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Airbnb%2C%20the%20patchwork%20regulation%20around%20the%20world%20is%20both%20%26quot%3Ba%20problem%20and%20an%20opportunity%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Cox.%20If%20rentals%20are%20curtailed%20in%20Paris%2C%20the%20company%20could%20look%20to%20expand%20to%20nearby%20cities%20or%20rural%20parts%20of%20France%20where%20there%20are%20fewer%20regulations.%20For%20Airbnb%2C%20that%20might%20mean%20moving%20into%20new%20countries.%20%26quot%3BThey%20either%20can't%20grow%20or%20they're%20declining%20in%20cities%20or%20some%20parts%26quot%3B%20of%20their%20core%20markets%2C%20Cox%20says.%20%26quot%3BThe%20only%20way%20that%20they%20can%20either%20maintain%20their%20revenues%20or%20grow%20is%20to%20push%20into%20other%20markets.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAirbnb%20isn't%20opposed%20to%20rules%20outright.%20If%20regulations%20are%20in%20place%20%3Cem%3Ebefore%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20company%20expands%20to%20a%20new%20market%2C%20it%20could%20make%20the%20process%20simpler%20for%20hosts%20and%20guests%20and%20spare%20Airbnb%20from%20having%20to%20pivot%20and%20wipe%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20listings%20from%20its%20platform%20in%20one%20swoop%20%3Cem%3Eafter%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20new%20law%20passes.%20%26quot%3BWe%20really%20do%20welcome%20sensible%20regulation%2C%26quot%3B%20Stephenson%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BIn%20a%20sensible%2C%20reasonable%20way%2C%20it%20works%20quite%20well.%26quot%3B%20Airbnb%20is%20still%20pushing%20back%20against%20what%20it%20believes%20are%20overreaching%20regulations%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairbnb-numbers-shrink-hotel-prices-soar-ban-nyc-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethose%20in%20New%20York%20City%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20despite%20the%20regulations%2C%20Airbnb%20is%20growing.%20Its%20revenue%20is%20up%2010%25%20year%20over%20year%2C%20and%20the%20number%20of%20nights%20booked%20grew%2C%20along%20with%20experiences%2C%20which%20include%20activities%20provided%20by%20local%20businesses%20and%20tour%20guides%2C%20by%208%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Airbnb's%20challenges%20don't%20stop%20at%20the%20regulations.%20It%20must%20also%20get%20people%20around%20the%20world%20to%20buy%20in.%20%26quot%3BEach%20country%20is%20going%20to%20have%20its%20own%20dynamics%2C%26quot%3B%20Jamie%20Lane%2C%20the%20senior%20vice%20president%20of%20analytics%20and%20chief%20economist%20at%20AirDNA%2C%20tells%20me.%20In%20some%20countries%2C%20hosting%20strangers%20in%20your%20home%20wouldn't%20be%20culturally%20acceptable.%20Lane%20also%20says%20there%20are%20local%20competitors%20to%20Airbnb%20in%20some%20places%20%26quot%3Bthat%20have%20been%20impactful%20and%20made%20it%20hard%20for%20them%20to%20compete.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20challenges%20are%20partially%20why%20Airbnb%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairbnb-leaving-china-citizens-unfazed-reactions-rental-listings-2022-5%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAirbnb%2520will%2520be%2520removing%2520all%2Cin%2520its%25202020%2520SEC%2520report.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epulled%20out%20of%20hosting%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20China%20in%202022%2C%20wiping%20out%20150%2C000%20listings%20there.%20For%20one%2C%20the%20country's%20strict%20travel%20regulations%20around%20COVID-19%20lasted%20longer%20than%20measures%20taken%20by%20most%20other%20nations%2C%20which%20created%20a%20drag%20on%20travel%20bookings.%20But%20Airbnb%20struggled%20to%20compete%20with%20Chinese%20companies%20offering%20short-term%20rentals%20long%20before%20that.%20The%20homegrown%20alternatives%20there%20included%20Tujia%2C%20which%20was%20designed%20to%20attract%20Chinese%20travelers%20specifically%20by%20anticipating%20peak%20travel%20times%20and%20rates%2C%20Melissa%20Yang%2C%20the%20company's%20cofounder%2C%20told%20CNN%20several%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChesky%20is%20more%20confident%20that%20Airbnb%20can%20win%20over%20the%20hearts%20and%20minds%20of%20the%20masses%20anywhere%20it%20goes.%20%26quot%3BAirbnb%20pretty%20much%20resonates%20pretty%20equally%20everywhere%20once%20there's%20the%20awareness%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20investors%20in%20a%20call%20earlier%20this%20year.%20%26quot%3BIn%20fact%2C%20I%20could%20argue%20that%20Airbnb%20might%20resonate%20better%20in%20Asia%20because%20there's%20a%20younger%20travel%20population%20that's%20not%20predisposed%20to%20hotels%2C%20and%20they're%20on%20social%20media.%20And%20we%20are%20disproportionately%20on%20social%20media%20versus%20our%20competitors.%20So%20I'm%20very%2C%20very%20bullish%20about%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20company%20isn't%20telegraphing%20its%20expansion%20strategy%20in%20every%20country%2C%20one%20of%20its%20most%20obvious%20moves%20began%20in%20Japan%20this%20fall.%20Airbnb%20ran%20an%20ad%20in%20English%20last%20year%20promoting%20travel%20in%20Kyoto%2C%20but%20it%20ramped%20up%20its%20Japanese%20ads%20in%20October.%20It's%20looking%20to%20court%20young%20Japanese%20travelers%20who%20want%20to%20take%20weekend%20trips%2C%20showing%20photos%20of%20a%20family%20traveling%20to%20a%20sleek%2C%20modern%20cabin%20in%20a%20wooded%20area%2C%20where%20they%20sing%20karaoke.%20Stephenson%20says%20Airbnb%20has%20also%20learned%20that%20local%20travelers%20want%20proximity%20to%20onsens%2C%20Japanese%20hot%20springs%20and%20bathing%20facilities%2C%20so%20listings%20there%20now%20show%20nearby%20onsens.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EElsewhere%2C%20Airbnb%20has%20been%20implementing%20payment%20methods%20preferred%20by%20locals.%20The%20company%20recently%20added%20KaKao%20Pay%20in%20South%20Korea%20and%20Vipps%20in%20Norway%2C%20among%20dozens%20of%20other%20options.%20It%20may%20seem%20like%20a%20small%20step%2C%20but%20Airbnb%20thinks%20meeting%20people%20where%20and%20how%20they%20pay%20will%20make%20the%20service%20more%20appealing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20are%20closely%20watching%20Airbnb's%20ongoing%20spread.%20Bianca%20Tavolari%2C%20a%20researcher%20and%20member%20of%20the%20advisory%20board%20of%20the%20Global%20Observatory%20of%20Short-Term%20Rentals%2C%20a%20group%20of%20Latin%20American%20organizations%20focused%20on%20housing%2C%20says%20Brazil%20has%20lagged%20in%20regulating%20short-term%20rentals%2C%20though%20a%20court%20ruled%20last%20year%20that%20hosts%20must%20have%20explicit%20consent%20from%20property%20owners%20to%20list%20apartments%20or%20condos%20as%20short-term%20rentals.%20Airbnb%20shares%20some%20tourism%20trend%20information%20with%20local%20officials%20through%20its%20city%20portal%2C%20but%20researchers%20like%20Tavolari%20still%20have%20questions%20about%20Airbnb's%20full%20impact.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20in%20the%20dark%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20tells%20me.%20Yet%20%26quot%3Bcities%20are%20seeing%20it%20as%20a%20great%20opportunity%2C%26quot%3B%20particularly%20those%20that%20depend%20heavily%20on%20tourism%20dollars%2C%20she%20says%2C%20and%20thinking%20less%20about%20the%20long-term%20costs%20to%20residents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECox%20says%20he's%20%26quot%3Bhopeful%20that%20some%20of%20these%20locations%20that%20Airbnb%20is%20planning%20to%20push%20to%20have%20already%20started%20thinking%20about%26quot%3B%20how%20they'll%20handle%20its%20growth.%20If%20Chesky's%20hypothesis%20is%20right%2C%20Airbnb%20could%20continue%20to%20spread%20rapidly%20once%20people%20in%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20world%20get%20used%20to%20couch%20surfing%20or%20navigating%20a%20hidden%20lockbox%20to%20let%20themselves%20into%20their%20rentals.%20Cities%20should%20be%20ready%20before%20more%20tourists%20start%20packing%20their%20bags.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Famanda-hoover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAmanda%20Hoover%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%20covering%20the%20tech%20industry.%20She%20writes%20about%20the%20biggest%20tech%20companies%20and%20trends.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairbnb-global-dominance-brazil-china-japan-chesky-cities-regulation-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734253681000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F675b405bcf8d1359a2df965a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairbnb-global-dominance-brazil-china-japan-chesky-cities-regulation-2024-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22American%20cities%20are%20cracking%20down%20on%20Airbnb%20%E2%80%94%20so%20it's%20expanding%20rapidly%20in%20countries%20like%20Mexico%2C%20Japan%2C%20South%20Korea%2C%20and%20Italy.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ahoover%40insider.com%20(Amanda%20Hoover)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairbnb-global-dominance-brazil-china-japan-chesky-cities-regulation-2024-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Their%20mother%20inherited%20a%20priceless%20archive.%20The%20battle%20to%20control%20it%20tore%20the%20family%20apart.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20illustration%20of%20The%20Duchess%20and%20her%20children%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F674deadfe45a68623a276953%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Red%20Duchess%2C%20as%20she%20was%20known%2C%20planned%20for%20her%20lover%2C%20not%20her%20three%20children%2C%20to%20inherit%20the%20archive%20she%20tended%20for%20much%20of%20her%20life.%3Cp%3ENate%20Sweitzer%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20Leoncio%20Alonso%20Gonz%C3%A1lez%20de%20Gregorio%20y%20%C3%81lvarez%20de%20Toledo%2C%20the%2022nd%20Duke%20of%20Medina%20Sidonia%2C%20stormed%20into%20his%20late%20mother's%20palace%20on%20the%20Andalusian%20coast%20of%20Spain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20video%20he%20posted%20on%20YouTube%20marking%20the%20occasion%2C%20the%20Duke%2C%20tall%20and%20silver-haired%2C%20strides%20triumphantly%20through%20the%20Ambassador%20Room%20%E2%80%94%20a%20grand%20hall%20nearly%2033%20yards%20long%2C%20lined%20with%20oil%20paintings%20by%20the%20likes%20of%20Vel%C3%A1zquez's%20master%2C%20Francisco%20Pacheco.%20In%20happier%20times%2C%20the%20room%20had%20been%20used%20for%20receiving%20dignitaries%20who%20visited%20the%20Duke's%20mother%2C%20Luisa%20Isabel%20%C3%81lvarez%20de%20Toledo.%20Celebrated%20as%20the%20%26quot%3BRed%20Duchess%2C%26quot%3B%20Luisa%20Isabel%20was%20a%20socialist-minded%2C%20fascism-battling%20aristocrat%20beloved%20by%20ordinary%20Spaniards.%20But%20now%2C%2011%20years%20after%20she%20had%20cut%20Leonicio%20and%20his%20siblings%20out%20of%20their%20inheritance%2C%20the%20Duke%20had%20arrived%20at%20the%20palace%20to%20lay%20claim%20to%20a%20national%20treasure%20he%20considered%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvacation-home-country-house-inheritance-trusts-estates-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehis%20by%20birthright%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20last%2C%20I'm%20at%20home%20after%20many%20decades%20away%2C%26quot%3B%20Leoncio%20proclaims%20in%20the%20video.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20treasure%2C%20known%20as%20the%20Archive%20of%20Medina-Sidonia%2C%20was%20housed%20in%20the%20palace's%20attic.%20A%20collection%20of%206%20million%20documents%2C%20it%20spans%20nearly%20a%20millennium%20of%20Spanish%20imperial%20history.%20Within%20its%20pages%20lie%20the%20secrets%20of%20the%20kings%2C%20dukes%2C%20and%20explorers%20of%20medieval%20Spain.%20Luisa%20Isabel%2C%20who%20had%20spent%20the%20last%20two%20decades%20of%20her%20life%20cataloging%20the%20archive%2C%20believed%20it%20proved%20that%20Arab%20Andalusians%2C%20not%20Christopher%20Columbus%2C%20had%20discovered%20America.%20Perhaps%20the%20most%20important%20privately%20held%20archive%20in%20Europe%2C%20it%20is%20valued%20at%20over%20%2460%20million%2C%20though%20historians%20who%20have%20studied%20it%20consider%20it%20priceless.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELuisa%20Isabel%2C%20who'd%20been%20imprisoned%20under%20the%20regime%20of%20dictator%20Francisco%20Franco%2C%20believed%20the%20archive%20should%20pass%20to%20the%20people.%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20inherited%20this%20legacy%2C%20which%20is%20legally%20mine%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20once%20declared.%20%26quot%3BBut%20morally%2C%20it%20belongs%20to%20everyone.%26quot%3B%20In%20her%20will%2C%20Luisa%20Isabel%20left%20only%20743%2C000%20euros%20to%20Leoncio%20and%20his%20siblings%2C%20Pilar%20and%20Gabriel.%20The%20bulk%20of%20the%20estate%20%E2%80%94%20including%20the%20archives%20%E2%80%94%20would%20be%20controlled%20by%20Liliane%20Dahlmann%2C%20Luisa%20Isabel's%20lover%20and%20longtime%20secretary%2C%20whom%20the%20Duchess%20had%20married%20on%20her%20deathbed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20ensued%20was%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwealthy-family-office-rich-heirs-succession-planning-jpmorgan-survey-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebitter%20legal%20battle%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20would%20shatter%20the%20family%2C%20captivate%20Spanish%20society%2C%20and%20throw%20the%20fate%20of%20the%20archive%20into%20doubt.%20Leoncio's%20homecoming%20video%20was%20a%20declaration%20of%20war.%20Flouting%20a%20court%20ruling%20that%20barred%20him%20and%20his%20siblings%20from%20living%20in%20the%20palace%2C%20he%20had%20decided%20to%20move%20back%20into%20his%20ancestral%20home%20%E2%80%94%20even%20though%20it%20was%20legally%20occupied%20by%20Liliane%2C%20his%20mother's%20widow.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20tension%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Gabriel%2C%20the%20black%20sheep%20of%20the%20family.%20%26quot%3BThey%20barely%20talk%20to%20one%20another%2C%20enter%20and%20leave%20through%20separate%20doors%2C%20and%20rarely%20bump%20into%20one%20another.%26quot%3B%20To%20drive%20home%20his%20disputed%20claim%2C%20Leoncio%20made%20a%20point%20of%20interrupting%20weekly%20palace%20tours.%20%26quot%3BWelcome%20to%20my%20house!%26quot%3B%20he%20would%20greet%20groups%20of%20startled%20tourists.%20%26quot%3BHere%2C%20they%20only%20manipulate%20the%20truth.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELiliane%2C%20ensconced%20upstairs%20with%20the%20archive%20she%20had%20been%20charged%20with%20safeguarding%2C%20kept%20her%20silence.%20At%20times%20it%20must%20have%20seemed%20that%20the%20family's%20inheritance%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flife-coach-for-ultrawealthy-children-facing-three-issues-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epassed%20down%20through%20the%20generations%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20now%20entrusted%20to%20her%20care%2C%20was%20cursed.%20%26quot%3BSometimes%20you%20don't%20choose%20your%20destiny%2C%20it%20chooses%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20once%20said.%20%26quot%3BPersonally%2C%20these%20past%20few%20years%20have%20been%20exceedingly%20difficult%20%E2%80%94%20the%20stuff%20of%20nightmares.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20family%20appeared%20to%20start%20off%20happily%20enough.%20In%201955%2C%20only%2018%20years%20old%20and%20already%20pregnant%20with%20Leoncio%2C%20Luisa%20Isabel%20married%20Jos%C3%A9%20Leoncio%20Gonz%C3%A1lez%20de%20Gregorio%2C%20a%20nobleman%20from%20Soria.%20Photographs%20from%20the%20time%20show%20the%20new%20Duchess%20smiling%20in%20a%20black%20ankle-length%20dress%2C%20her%20long%20hair%20framing%20her%20tiny%20face%20and%20her%20lips%20brightened%20with%20lipstick.%20Standing%20beside%20her%2C%20Jos%C3%A9%20Leoncio%20appears%20tall%2C%20athletic%2C%20and%20handsome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20reality%2C%20Luisa%20Isabel%20and%20Jos%C3%A9%20Leoncio%20couldn't%20have%20made%20a%20more%20ill-suited%20couple.%20Her%20ancestors%20had%20commanded%20Spanish%20armadas%2C%20served%20as%20prime%20minister%2C%20and%20owned%20vast%20swathes%20of%20southern%20Spain.%20Her%20parents%20had%20fled%20the%20country%20during%20the%20Spanish%20Civil%20War.%20Her%20new%20husband%2C%20by%20contrast%2C%20was%20a%20die-hard%20conservative%20who%20supported%20Franco's%20dictatorship.%20Luisa%20Isabel%20loved%20the%20night%20life.%20Jos%C3%A9%20Leoncio%2C%20a%20man%20of%20the%20countryside%2C%20disliked%20high%20society%20nearly%20as%20much%20as%20the%20radical%20ideals%20that%20would%20soon%20claim%20his%20wife.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20their%20brief%20union%2C%20the%20couple%20had%20three%20children%20in%20quick%20succession%3A%20Leoncio%20in%201956%2C%20Pilar%20in%201957%2C%20and%20Gabriel%20in%201958.%20But%20the%20Duchess%20never%20seemed%20to%20take%20to%20the%20role%20of%20mother.%20After%20giving%20birth%20to%20Gabriel%2C%20family%20lore%20has%20it%20that%20she%20handed%20him%20to%20the%20nurses%20and%20declared%20she%20had%20fulfilled%20her%20role%20as%20a%20woman.%20The%20moment%20also%20marked%20the%20end%20of%20her%20marriage.%20Within%20the%20year%2C%20she%20had%20separated%20from%20Jos%C3%A9%20Leoncio%20and%20began%20to%20spend%20long%20stretches%20in%20Paris%2C%20where%20she%20mingled%20with%20Simone%20de%20Beauvoir%20and%20other%20leading%20intellectuals.%20Her%20children%20remained%20behind%20in%20Madrid%2C%20where%20they%20were%20left%20in%20the%20care%20of%20Luisa%20Isabel's%20grandmother.%20%26quot%3BShe%20rarely%20came%20to%20visit%2C%26quot%3B%20Gabriel%20recalls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20day%2C%20when%20Gabriel%20was%206%20or%207%2C%20his%20mother%20appeared%20at%20the%20door.%20Gone%20were%20her%20elegant%20dresses%20and%20long%20hair.%20Wafer%20thin%2C%20Luisa%20Isabel%20now%20sported%20men's%20trousers%20and%20short-cropped%20hair.%20There%20were%20rumors%20she%20was%20sleeping%20with%20women.%20%26quot%3BSomeone%20in%20the%20household%20said%20she%20was%20our%20mother%2C%26quot%3B%20Gabriel%20recalls.%20%26quot%3BBut%20for%20us%2C%20she%20looked%20like%20the%20boy%20who%20worked%20at%20the%20local%20grocery.%26quot%3B%20Leoncio%20was%20distraught.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20not%20my%20mother!%26quot%3B%20he%20cried.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20change%20in%20Luisa%20Isabel%20ran%20deeper%20than%20fashion.%20In%201964%2C%20the%20Duchess%20led%20a%20protest%20march%20of%20fishermen%20in%20Sanl%C3%BAcar.%20Her%20noble%20pedigree%20gave%20her%20a%20measure%20of%20protection%20to%20speak%20out%20against%20Franco.%20%26quot%3BThis%20privileged%20aristocrat%20had%20a%20rebellious%20spirit%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20one%20newspaper%20put%20it.%20Her%20reputation%20was%20further%20cemented%20in%201967%2C%20when%20she%20stood%20up%20for%20a%20group%20of%20protesters%20whose%20homes%20had%20been%20rendered%20radioactive%20after%20an%20American%20nuclear%20bomber%20crashed%20over%20the%20small%20fishing%20village%20of%20Palomares.%20The%20protesters%2C%20she%20told%20soldiers%20dispatched%20by%20the%20regime%2C%20%26quot%3Bare%20here%20only%20for%20justice%2C%20and%20they%20are%20here%20with%20me.%26quot%3B%20She%20then%20led%20the%20group%20to%20a%20bar%20at%20the%20village's%20main%20square%20for%20a%20round%20of%20cold%20beers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221774%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Duchess%20in%20a%20jail%20cell%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F674deb66e45a68623a276984%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221993%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDespite%20her%20noble%20pedigree%2C%20the%20Duchess%20was%20imprisoned%20for%20speaking%20out%20against%20Franco.%3Cp%3ENate%20Sweitzer%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EArrested%20and%20thrown%20in%20prison%20for%20a%20year%2C%20the%20Duchess%20kept%20up%20the%20fight%20from%20her%20miserable%2C%20rat-infested%20cell.%20She%20wrote%20letters%20and%20articles%20denouncing%20the%20conditions%20in%20Spanish%20prisons.%20A%20novel%20she%20authored%20about%20suffering%20farm%20workers%20called%20%26quot%3BThe%20Strike%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20she%20had%20managed%20to%20smuggle%20into%20France%2C%20prompted%20the%20government%20to%20threaten%20her%20with%20a%2010-year%20sentence%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efor%20slander.%20In%20April%201970%2C%20a%20few%20months%20after%20her%20release%2C%20the%20Duchess%20escaped%20to%20France%20disguised%20as%20a%20man.%20%26quot%3BI%20remember%20putting%20the%20hat%20and%20the%20mustache%20on%20her%2C%26quot%3B%20recalls%20Julia%20Franco%2C%20a%20longtime%20family%20employee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20her%20exile%2C%20Jos%C3%A9%20Leoncio%20seized%20on%20her%20political%20dissidence%20to%20secure%20custody%20of%20the%20children.%20%26quot%3BThe%20role%20of%20being%20a%20mother%20slipped%20away%20from%20her%2C%26quot%3B%20Pilar%20recalls.%20According%20to%20Gabriel%2C%20he%20and%20his%20siblings%20were%20at%20their%20father's%20mercy.%20%26quot%3BHe%20was%20determined%20to%20redirect%20our%20lives%2C%20banning%20the%20staff%20from%20passing%20her%20calls%20or%20letters%20on%20to%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20The%20children%2C%20by%20birth%2C%20were%20nobility.%20But%20their%20lives%20felt%20anything%20but%20noble.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Red%20Duchess%20Returns%26quot%3B%20blared%20a%20headline%20in%20El%20Pais%2C%20a%20national%20newspaper%2C%20in%201976.%20Franco%20had%20died%2C%20paving%20the%20way%20for%20Spain's%20first%20open%20elections%20in%20four%20decades%20and%20the%20safe%20return%20of%20Spanish%20dissidents.%20Luisa%20Isabel%20moved%20into%20the%20palace%20at%20Sanl%C3%BAcar%2C%20where%20she%20held%20court%20each%20evening%20surrounded%20by%20famous%20actors%2C%20foreign%20journalists%2C%20and%20celebrated%20academics.%20No%20longer%20closeted%20about%20her%20sexuality%2C%20she%20came%20across%20like%20a%20Spanish%20version%20of%20Sid%20Vicious.%20%26quot%3BShe%20was%20punky%2C%20with%20short%2C%20spiky%20hair%20and%20worn-out%20clothing%2C%26quot%3B%20recalls%20Miguel%20%26quot%3BEl%20Capi%26quot%3B%20Arenas%2C%20who%20lived%20with%20the%20Duchess%20in%20the%20early%201980s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20day%2C%20Luisa%20Isabel%20devoted%20herself%20to%20organizing%20the%20archives.%20Often%20rising%20at%206%20in%20the%20morning%2C%20she%20would%20sequester%20herself%20in%20the%20attic%20among%20stacks%20of%20dusty%20documents%2C%20chain-smoking%20cigarettes%20%E2%80%94%20two%20packs%20a%20day%20%E2%80%94%20and%20barely%20eating.%20She%20spent%20years%20cataloging%20the%20papers%20in%20jaundiced%20folders%2C%20tying%20them%20up%20with%20string%20and%20developing%20a%20knack%20for%20deciphering%20their%20Gothic%20cursive%20handwriting%2C%20with%20all%20its%20loops%20and%20ligatures.%20Establishing%20herself%20as%20an%20amateur%20historian%2C%20she%20published%20a%20dozen%20books%2C%20including%20%26quot%3BIt%20Wasn't%20Us%2C%26quot%3B%20her%20reappraisal%20of%20Columbus%20published%20on%20the%20500th%20anniversary%20of%20his%20arrival%20in%20America.%20Historians%20came%20to%20admire%20her%20patience%20and%20diligence.%20%26quot%3BShe%20did%20a%20magnificent%20job%20with%20very%20few%20resources%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Juan%20Luis%20Albentosa%2C%20chief%20archivist%20of%20the%20Franciscan%20Library%20in%20Murcia.%20%26quot%3BShe%20had%20no%20state%20support%20back%20then%2C%20nor%20any%20formal%20training.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Duchess%20had%20first%20encountered%20the%20papers%20in%20the%20late%201950s%20in%20a%20storage%20tunnel%20at%20her%20family%20home%20in%20Madrid%20and%20transported%20them%20to%20the%20palace%20in%20Sanl%C3%BAcar%20in%20the%20back%20of%20a%20lorry.%20While%20it%20wasn't%20unusual%20for%20noble%20families%20to%20maintain%20private%20archives%2C%20this%20one%20encompassed%20the%20unwritten%20history%20of%20Spain%20itself.%20The%20archive%20contained%20not%20only%20the%20records%20of%20various%20aristocratic%20families%2C%20but%20also%20receipts%20signed%20by%20the%20painter%20Diego%20Vel%C3%A1zquez%2C%20primary%20sources%20about%20the%20Spanish%20Armada%2C%20and%20municipal%20records%20from%20Palos%20de%20la%20Frontera%2C%20the%20village%20from%20which%20Columbus%20set%20sail%20in%201492.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Duchess%20both%20embraced%20and%20defied%20her%20status%20as%20an%20aristocrat.%20She%20believed%20the%20Archive%20of%20Medina-Sidonia%20belonged%20to%20the%20public%20%E2%80%94%20but%20only%20after%20she%20was%20no%20longer%20alive%20to%20claim%20it.%20%26quot%3BShe%20was%20a%20traditionalist%2C%26quot%3B%20her%20nephew%2C%20Alfonso%20Maura%2C%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BHow%20could%20she%20spend%20all%20those%20years%20working%20on%20the%20family%20archives%20and%20not%20be%3F%26quot%3B%20Andres%20Martinez%2C%20a%20historian%20and%20friend%20of%20the%20Duchess%2C%20casts%20her%20contradictory%20nature%20in%20more%20poetic%20terms.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20jump%20out%20of%20your%20own%20shadow%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Luisa%20Isabel%20devoted%20her%20days%20to%20the%20archive%20and%20her%20nights%20to%20her%20soirees%2C%20her%20children%20saw%20her%20only%20occasionally.%20To%20the%20Duchess%2C%20they%20were%20reminders%20of%20their%20father%20%E2%80%94%20and%20of%20the%20world%20of%20entitlement%20she%20had%20devoted%20her%20life%20to%20rejecting.%20In%201977%2C%20a%20year%20after%20her%20return%20to%20Spain%2C%20she%20wrote%20to%20the%20director%20general%20of%20the%20Spanish%20National%20Heritage%20Board%20to%20request%20that%20the%20palace%20and%20its%20contents%2C%20including%20the%20archives%2C%20be%20registered%20as%20protected%20public%20goods%2C%20to%20%26quot%3Bprevent%20losing%20what%20belongs%20to%20everyone.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20family's%20wealth%20isn't%20important%2C%20and%20my%20children%20don't%20seem%20interested%20in%20preserving%20our%20artistic%20heritage%2C%20although%20they%20enjoy%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote.%20By%20the%20following%20year%2C%20the%20request%20had%20been%20granted.%20The%20most%20important%20and%20valuable%20asset%20of%20Medina-Sidonia's%20ancestral%20heritage%20was%20now%20under%20the%20protection%20of%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Gabriel's%20view%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20moment%20that%20marked%20our%20disunion%26quot%3B%20occurred%20in%201982%20%E2%80%94%20the%20day%20Leoncio%20married%20his%20first%20wife%2C%20a%20Catalonian%20aristocrat%20named%20Mar%C3%ADa%20Montserrat%20Vi%C3%B1amata%20y%20Martorell.%20It%20was%20at%20the%20wedding%20that%20Liliane%20Dahlmann%2C%20one%20of%20the%20bridesmaids%2C%20entered%20Luisa%20Isabel's%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Duchess%20noticed%20Liliane%20immediately.%20Tall%20and%20blonde%20and%2020%20years%20Luisa%20Isabel's%20junior%2C%20Liliane%20had%20moved%20from%20Germany%20to%20Barcelona%20as%20a%20girl.%20%26quot%3BI'll%20make%20her%20mine%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Duchess%20told%20her%20friend%20Capi%20Arenas%20during%20the%20reception.%20Julia%20Franco%2C%20who%20was%20also%20in%20attendance%2C%20recalls%20that%20the%20Duchess%20and%20Liliane%20%26quot%3Bcouldn't%20take%20their%20eyes%20off%20each%20other.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20long%2C%20Liliane%20had%20moved%20into%20the%20palace%2C%20where%20she%20served%20as%20Luisa%20Isabel's%20secretary.%20The%20relationship%20mellowed%20the%20Duchess.%20Gone%20were%20the%20wild%20parties%20and%20the%20bohemian%20friends%20crashing%20at%20the%20palace%20for%20months%20on%20end%3B%20Luisa%20Isabel%20became%20quieter%20and%20more%20dedicated%20to%20the%20archives.%20%26quot%3BThey%20were%20always%20together%2C%26quot%3B%20her%20friend%20Andres%20Martinez%20recalls.%20%26quot%3BI%20couldn't%20get%20the%20Duchess%20alone%2C%20ever.%26quot%3B%20Luisa%20Isabel's%20children%20were%20also%20suspicious.%20%26quot%3BLiliane%20was%20always%20in%20my%20mother's%20ear%2C%20trying%20to%20make%20us%20look%20bad%2C%26quot%3B%20Pillar%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20children%20also%20began%20to%20fight%20among%20themselves.%20As%20the%20eldest%2C%20Leoncio%20had%20a%20role%20in%20deciding%20which%20family%20titles%20went%20to%20whom.%20Gabriel%20claims%20they%20had%20an%20understanding%20that%20he%20would%20be%20named%20Duke%20of%20Montalto%20and%20Aragon%2C%20and%20that%20Leoncio%20had%20changed%20his%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20inclined%20to%20stop%20the%20progressive%20scattering%20of%20our%20family%20titles%2C%26quot%3B%20Leoncio%20wrote%20in%20a%20letter%20to%20his%20brother%2C%20rationalizing%20the%20decision.%20Since%20the%20family%20could%20no%20longer%20claim%20economic%20or%20political%20power%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bmoral%20and%20historical%20integrity%20is%20all%20we%20have%20left.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPilar%20was%20next.%20In%201993%2C%20King%20Juan%20Carlos%20I%20had%20named%20her%20Duchess%20of%20Fernandina.%20Now%2C%20Leoncio%20maintained%20that%20the%20title%20should%20have%20gone%20to%20his%20son.%20He%20launched%20a%20battle%20in%20the%20Spanish%20courts%2C%20stripping%20his%20sister%20of%20her%20noble%20name%20and%20privileges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeoncio%20also%20squabbled%20with%20his%20mother%20over%20the%20estate%20of%20her%20grandmother%2C%20who%20had%20left%20the%20children%20an%20inheritance%20%26quot%3Bworth%20millions%20of%20euros%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20Gabriel.%20But%20as%20the%20estate's%20administrator%2C%20the%20Duchess%20had%20spent%20much%20of%20the%20money.%20In%20a%20letter%20to%20his%20mother%2C%20Leoncio%20protested%20this%20%26quot%3Brobbery%2C%26quot%3B%20complaining%20that%20he%20had%20received%20no%20financial%20help%20after%20his%20marriage%20and%20the%20birth%20of%20his%20son.%20He%20barely%20mentioned%20Pilar%20and%20Gabriel.%20The%20Duchess%2C%20in%20a%20scathing%20reply%2C%20denounced%20Leoncio%20as%20%26quot%3Bweaker%26quot%3B%20than%20she%20had%20%26quot%3Bever%20imagined.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGabriel%20had%20considered%20himself%20and%20Leoncio%20thick%20as%20thieves%3B%20they%20had%20lived%20together%20during%20their%20university%20days%20in%20Madrid%20and%20always%20looked%20after%20each%20other.%20Now%2C%20he%20felt%20that%20Leoncio%20was%20only%20looking%20out%20for%20himself.%20Pilar%20agreed.%20%26quot%3BMy%20older%20brother%20tried%20to%20keep%20everything%20for%20himself%20and%20push%20us%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGabriel%20and%20Pilar%20took%20the%20nuclear%20option.%20In%201989%2C%20they%20successfully%20sued%20their%20mother%20over%20the%20misspent%20money.%20In%20retaliation%2C%20the%20Duchess%20banned%20them%20from%20the%20palace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20ensuing%20years%2C%20the%20Duchess%20sold%20off%20various%20tracts%20of%20land%20and%20other%20assets%2C%20reinvesting%20the%20money%20in%20the%20palace%2C%20and%20took%20steps%20to%20ensure%20that%20none%20of%20the%20children%20would%20have%20any%20power%20over%20the%20archives.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIn%201990%2C%20she%20transferred%20ownership%20of%20the%20palace%20and%20the%20archives%20to%20a%20new%20organization%20she%20founded%2C%20the%20Casa%20Medina%20Sidonia%20Foundation.%20And%20in%202005%2C%20she%20amended%20the%20foundation's%20statutes%20to%20ensure%20that%2C%20upon%20her%20death%2C%20Liliane%20would%20take%20over%20as%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThree%20years%20later%2C%20on%20the%20night%20the%20Duchess%20died%20%E2%80%94%20March%207%2C%202008%20%E2%80%94%20mourners%20filled%20the%20Salon%20of%20Columns%2C%20a%20vast%20room%20in%20the%20palace%20crafted%20by%20American%20artisans%20provided%20to%20the%20family%20by%20the%2016th-century%20conquistador%20Hern%C3%A1n%20Cort%C3%A9s.%20Gabriel%20arrived%20at%20around%2010%20o'clock%20at%20night.%20At%20age%2050%2C%20he%20and%20his%20mother%20hadn't%20spoken%20in%2020%20years.%20Leoncio%20and%20Pilar%20were%20already%20there.%20The%20greetings%20between%20them%20were%20civil%20but%20not%20warm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20whispers%20about%20how%20the%20Duchess%20had%20carried%20out%20one%20final%20snub%20of%20her%20children.%20Just%2011%20hours%20before%20her%20death%2C%20she%20had%20married%20Liliane%20in%20a%20civil%20ceremony.%20Details%20of%20the%20wedding%20were%20hush-hush%2C%20but%20it%20granted%20Liliane%20legal%20control%20of%20the%20palace%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20archives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGabriel%20had%20arrived%20at%20the%20palace%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewith%20a%20somewhat%20macabre%20mission%20in%20mind.%20He'd%20brought%20a%20camera%20with%20him%2C%20and%20he%20planned%20to%20capture%20an%20image%20of%20his%20mother's%20corpse%2C%20just%20as%20he'd%20done%20when%20his%20father%20had%20died%20a%20month%20earlier.%20He%20wasn't%20sure%20where%20this%20impulse%20came%20from.%20Perhaps%2C%20after%20years%20of%20animosity%20and%20neglect%2C%20he%20wanted%20proof%20his%20parents%20were%20really%20gone%20for%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStepping%20away%20from%20the%20mourners%2C%20Gabriel%20entered%20the%20room%20where%20the%20Duchess%20lay%20in%20a%20casket.%20She%20was%20%26quot%3Bdeteriorated%2C%20stiff%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20recalls.%20He%20felt%20no%20despair%2C%20no%20sense%20of%20grief.%20He%20took%20the%20camera%20from%20his%20pocket%20and%20held%20it%20over%20her%20body.%20As%20he%20did%2C%20others%20in%20the%20room%20protested.%20Gabriel%20took%20the%20picture%20anyway.%20%26quot%3BHe%20had%20the%20right%20to%20take%20a%20photo%20of%20her%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20his%20friend%20%C3%8D%C3%B1igo%20Ram%C3%ADrez%20de%20Haro%2C%20an%20author%20and%20playwright%20who%20accompanied%20Gabriel%20that%20night.%20%26quot%3BHe%20was%20her%20son%2C%20after%20all.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221833%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Illustration%20of%20the%20funeral%20scene%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F674debf7e45a68623a2769b6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221951%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20night%20the%20Duchess%20died%2C%20her%20sons%20devolved%20into%20a%20fight%20over%20a%20photograph%20Gabriel%20took%20of%20her%20body.%3Cp%3ENate%20Sweitzer%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAlerted%20to%20what%20was%20happening%2C%20Leoncio%20suddenly%20appeared%20and%20began%20chasing%20his%20brother%20around%20the%20room.%20%26quot%3BHe%20asked%20me%20to%20delete%20the%20photo%2C%26quot%3B%20Gabriel%20recalls.%20It%20was%20a%20regression%20to%20youth%2C%20two%20middle-aged%20men%20sparring%20like%20adolescents%20in%20their%20mother's%20grand%20house.%20It%20was%20also%20a%20sign%20of%20the%20quarrels%20to%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20the%20siblings%20worked%20in%20concert%20to%20challenge%20their%20mother's%20will.%20In%20court%2C%20they%20cited%20a%20provision%20of%20Spanish%20law%20mandating%20that%20a%20person's%20descendants%20have%20a%20right%20to%20two-thirds%20of%20an%20estate%2C%20regardless%20of%20the%20deceased's%20wishes.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20surprised%20by%20any%20of%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20Gabriel%20told%20a%20reporter%20at%20the%20time.%20%26quot%3BMy%20mother%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20she%20was%20going%20to%20fuck%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20agreed.%20By%20transferring%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20her%20wealth%20%E2%80%94%20the%20palace%20and%20its%20contents%2C%20including%20the%20archives%20%E2%80%94%20to%20the%20foundation%2C%20the%20Duchess%20had%20exceeded%20the%20portion%20of%20her%20estate%20she%20was%20legally%20allowed%20to%20bequeath%20to%20non-heirs.%20The%20foundation%20was%20ordered%20to%20pay%2027%20million%20euros%20to%20the%20children%20as%20compensation.%20There%20was%20only%20one%20problem%3A%20The%20foundation%20had%20nowhere%20near%20that%20much%20money%2C%20and%2C%20as%20a%20national%20heritage%20site%2C%20none%20of%20it%20could%20be%20sold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20further%20complicate%20matters%2C%20Leoncio%20wasn't%20satisfied%20with%20the%20ruling.%20He%20was%20after%20something%20more%20than%20money.%20As%20duke%2C%20he%20believed%20he%20should%20be%20responsible%20for%20the%20palace%2C%20the%20archives%2C%20and%20the%20family%20legacy.%20%26quot%3BLeoncio%20Alonso%20wasn't%20happy%20with%20this%20solution%20because%20it%20meant%20giving%20up%20his%20family's%20property%2C%20and%20he%20didn't%20want%20to%20be%20remembered%20as%20the%20first%20Duke%20of%20Medina%20Sidonia%20to%20allow%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20Eduardo%20Ferreiro%2C%20Leoncio's%20lawyer%2C%20said%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeoncio%20appealed%20the%20ruling%20and%20won.%20But%20the%20victory%20proved%20pyrrhic.%20The%20higher%20court%20ruled%20that%20he%20and%20his%20siblings%20would%20become%20part%20owners%20of%20the%20palace%20and%20its%20treasures%20%E2%80%94%20though%20without%20any%20power%20over%20its%20administration%2C%20any%20right%20to%20distribute%20its%20contents%2C%20or%20any%20privilege%20to%20reside%20there.%20Liliane%2C%20the%20court%20added%2C%20could%20continue%20to%20live%20in%20the%20palace.%20The%20siblings%20were%20effectively%20owners%20of%20everything%2C%20and%20of%20nothing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInfuriated%2C%20Leoncio%20decided%20to%20defy%20the%20court's%20ruling%20and%20take%20matters%20into%20his%20own%20hands.%20He%20moved%20into%20the%20palace%2C%20effectively%20becoming%20housemates%20with%20his%20mother's%20widow.%20%26quot%3BCohabitation%20is%20uncomfortable%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20a%20reporter.%20%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20the%20house%20is%20big.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThings%20got%20messy%2C%20fast.%20A%20newspaper%20reported%20that%20Montserrat%20Vi%C3%B1amata%2C%20Leoncio's%20first%20wife%2C%20had%20become%20romantically%20involved%20with%20Liliane%2C%20whom%20she%20had%20known%20since%20their%20university%20days%20in%20Barcelona.%20Vi%C3%B1amata%20denied%20the%20rumor%3A%20%26quot%3BWhoever%20has%20insinuated%20this%20has%20done%20me%20a%20lot%20of%20damage%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20a%20local%20newspaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20Leoncio%20ratcheted%20up%20the%20dispute.%20He%20accused%20Liliane%20of%20taking%20money%20from%20his%20mother's%20estate.%20Liliane%20denied%20the%20charge%2C%20arguing%20that%20Leoncio%20was%20smearing%20her%20name%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20remove%20her%20as%20president%20of%20the%20foundation%20so%20he%20could%20take%20over%20in%20her%20place.%20Both%20of%20them%20declined%20requests%20to%20speak%20with%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20a%20judge%20found%20Liliane%20guilty%20of%20misappropriating%20funds.%20She%20was%20sentenced%20to%20six%20months%20in%20prison%20and%20ordered%20to%20repay%20280%2C000%20euros.%20Her%20appeal%20is%20due%20to%20be%20heard%20by%20Spain's%20supreme%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20hot%20morning%20last%20summer%2C%20I%20sit%20down%20with%20Gabriel%20at%20a%20busy%20caf%C3%A9%20terrace%20in%20Madrid.%20Dressed%20in%20navy%20blue%20shorts%20and%20a%20white%20polo%20shirt%2C%20collar%20up%2C%20he%20looks%20every%20inch%20the%20aristocrat.%20Slim%2C%20with%20wavy%20gray%20hair%2C%20he's%20the%20kind%20of%20well-read%20man%20who%20sprinkles%20his%20conversations%20with%20quotes%20from%20the%20French%20economist%20Thomas%20Piketty.%20He%20also%20takes%20after%20his%20mother.%20It's%20as%20if%20his%20obsession%20with%20her%20betrayal%20has%20so%20boiled%20within%20him%20that%20it%20now%20emanates%20from%20his%20very%20physicality.%20He%20has%20her%20rosy%20cheeks%2C%20her%20birdish%20eyes%2C%20her%20same%20stubborn%20drive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGabriel%2C%20divorced%20and%20childless%2C%20seems%20caught%20in%20a%20perpetual%20struggle%20to%20find%20his%20place%20in%20the%20world.%20He%20has%20a%20habit%20of%20talking%20in%20circles%2C%20though%20he%20always%20returns%20to%20the%20topic%20of%20how%20his%20family%20has%20been%20torn%20apart.%20%26quot%3BI've%20been%20at%20caf%C3%A9s%20with%20him%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20a%20close%20family%20member%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20suddenly%20he'll%20just%20start%20talking%20to%20someone%20he%20barely%20knows%20about%20his%20quarrels%20with%20his%20mother.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20mother%2C%20he%20tells%20me%2C%20%26quot%3Bnever%20wanted%20to%20have%20any%20relationship%20with%20us.%20Above%20all%2C%20she%20saw%20us%20as%20a%20threat%20to%20the%20free%20disposal%20of%20her%20wealth.%26quot%3B%20He%20claims%20he%20wants%20to%20mediate%20between%20his%20siblings%20and%20Liliane.%20%26quot%3BI%20see%20the%20foundation%20as%20running%20like%20a%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20interests%20me%20is%20that%20it's%20run%20well%2C%20not%20who%20runs%20it.%26quot%3B%20But%20even%20those%20closest%20to%20him%20have%20trouble%20discerning%20his%20true%20intentions.%20%26quot%3BGabriel's%20views%20on%20all%20this%20change%20%E2%80%94%20depending%20on%20how%20he%20wakes%20up%20in%20the%20morning%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20his%20good%20friend%20and%20lawyer%2C%20Javier%20Timmermans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPilar%2C%20for%20her%20part%2C%20sees%20the%20family%20drama%20as%20integral%20to%20both%20brothers'%20emotional%20makeup.%20Gabriel%20%26quot%3Bseems%20to%20be%20searching%20for%20headlines%20rather%20than%20solutions%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says%2C%20while%20Leoncio%20is%20%26quot%3Bjust%20interested%20in%20defending%20his%20claims%26quot%3B%20as%20the%20first-born%20son.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221544%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Illustration%20of%20the%20co%20inhabitance%20conflict%20within%20the%20palace%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F674dec217929f317fb4f9248%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221828%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAs%20Liliane%20and%20Leoncio%20battle%20for%20control%20of%20the%20archives%2C%20they%20continue%20to%20share%20the%20palace.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20tension%2C%26quot%3B%20observes%20Gabriel.%20%26quot%3BThey%20barely%20talk%20to%20one%20another.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ENate%20Sweitzer%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPilar%2C%20a%20writer%20and%20a%20socialite%2C%20inherited%20her%20mother's%20flair%20for%20culture%3A%20One%20paper%20called%20her%20%26quot%3Bpossibly%20the%20most%20elegant%20woman%20in%20Spanish%20high%20society.%26quot%3B%20If%20her%20brothers%20remain%20bent%20on%20getting%20justice%2C%20she's%20more%20interested%20in%20closure.%20%26quot%3BAll%20that%20sensationalism%20doesn't%20matter%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BThat%20might%20be%20fine%20for%20making%20a%20soap%20opera%20if%20they%20want%2C%20but%20solving%20the%20archives%20issue%20doesn't%20have%20to%20depend%20on%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPilar%20is%20the%20first%20to%20admit%20that%20she%20has%20good%20reason%20to%20seek%20a%20settlement.%20She%20has%20inherited%20her%20father's%20residence%20in%20central%20Spain%2C%20the%20Gonz%C3%A1lez%20de%20Gregorio%20Palace%2C%20and%20she%20has%20taken%20to%20referring%20to%20it%20as%20her%20vampire%20because%20it%20sucks%20up%20all%20her%20money.%20%26quot%3BI%20would%20be%20lying%20if%20I%20said%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20resolve%20this%20situation%20because%20I%20need%20to%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%20for%20Pilar%20and%20her%20brothers%2C%20their%20father's%20estate%20is%20proving%20every%20bit%20as%20thorny%20as%20their%20mother's.%20A%20half-sister%20whom%20their%20father%20never%20recognized%20has%20come%20forward%20to%20demand%20a%20share%20of%20his%20estate%2C%20using%20the%20same%20provision%20of%20Spanish%20inheritance%20law%20that%20they%20themselves%20deployed%20against%20the%20foundation.%20In%20October%2C%20a%20court%20ordered%20Pilar%20and%20her%20brothers%20to%20pay%20the%20half-sister%20a%20sum%20of%20more%20than%20%241%20million.%20Gabriel%20now%20fears%20they%20might%20be%20forced%20to%20auction%20off%20the%20rights%20to%20the%20archive%20to%20private%20bidders%20%E2%80%94%20a%20desperate%20measure%20to%20cover%20their%20spiraling%20debts.%20If%20that%20were%20to%20happen%2C%20the%20children%20would%20finally%20be%20separated%20from%20the%20archive%2C%20just%20as%20the%20Duchess%20had%20wanted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20months%20after%20meeting%20with%20Gabriel%2C%20I%20travel%20to%20Sanl%C3%BAcar%20de%20Barrameda%20to%20see%20the%20Archive%20of%20Medina%20Sidonia%20for%20myself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWalking%20through%20a%20labyrinth%20of%20narrow%20cobbled%20streets%20in%20the%20city%20center%2C%20I%20pass%20rows%20of%20simple%20white%20houses.%20Some%20of%20the%20facades%20are%20crumbling%20like%20stale%20bread%3B%20others%20are%20as%20pristine%20as%20a%20Hollywood%20smile.%20The%20whitewashed%20palace%20looms%20above%20the%20city%2C%20just%20as%20the%20family's%20thousand-year%20legacy%20has%20loomed%20over%20the%20children%20for%20their%20entire%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPast%20the%20sprawling%20Ambassador's%20Room%20where%20the%20Duke%20had%20filmed%20his%20triumphant%20return%2C%20I%20climb%20a%20flight%20of%20stairs%20to%20the%20attic.%20The%20Investigator's%20Room%20smells%20sweet%20and%20woody.%20A%20faint%20chill%20hangs%20in%20the%20air%2C%20and%20bright%20sunlight%20casts%20shadows%20across%20the%20high%20shelves%20lined%20with%20books.%20There%20I%20find%20Liliane%2C%20quietly%20tapping%20away%20on%20her%20laptop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20email%20to%20me%2C%20Liliane%20had%20accepted%20my%20request%20to%20visit%20the%20archive%2C%20but%20said%20she%20wouldn't%20comment%20on%20any%20legal%20matters%2C%20citing%20past%20experiences%20when%20she%20felt%20her%20words%20had%20been%20twisted.%20Her%20position%20on%20the%20archive%2C%20echoing%20that%20of%20the%20late%20Duchess%2C%20is%20that%20it%20belongs%20in%20public%20hands.%20%26quot%3BThey%20are%20the%20only%20ones%20who%2C%20today%2C%20can%20guarantee%20its%20maintenance%20and%20preservation%2C%20as%20required%20in%20a%20technological%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote%2C%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3Bknowledge%20of%20the%20past%20is%20indispensable%20for%20moving%20forward%20in%20all%20aspects%20of%20human%20life.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrue%20to%20her%20word%2C%20Liliane%20sits%20at%20the%20table%20beside%20me%20in%20silence%20while%20I%20study%20the%20archive.%20After%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eseveral%20hours%2C%20she%20abruptly%20leaves%20without%20uttering%20a%20word.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20handed%20an%20accountant's%20ledger%2C%20which%20indexes%20the%20documents%20in%20the%20archive%2C%20the%20descriptions%20scribbled%20in%20the%20margins%20in%20the%20Duchess's%20spidery%20handwriting.%20I%20ask%20for%20a%20diary%20of%20the%20Almadraba%20%E2%80%94%20the%20famous%20local%20fishing%20season%20held%20every%20May%20for%20the%20past%203%2C000%20years.%20The%20diary%20dates%20back%20to%201550%2C%20comprising%20a%20nearly%20indecipherable%20tabulation%20of%20the%20number%20of%20fish%20caught%2C%20and%20the%20money%20made%20in%20each%20village.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESitting%20with%20the%20nearly%20500-year-old%20document%20in%20the%20dim%20light%20of%20the%20library%2C%20I'm%20reminded%20that%20only%20a%20tiny%20part%20of%20the%20collection%20has%20been%20digitized.%20The%20history%20it%20contains%20is%20almost%20entirely%20physical.%20A%20fire%2C%20or%20a%20robbery%2C%20could%20cause%20the%20documents%20to%20disappear%20forever.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20viable%20resolution%20is%20for%20either%20the%20state%20or%20a%20major%20cultural%20institution%20to%20step%20in%20and%20buy%20the%20estate%20from%20the%20siblings%2C%20turning%20it%20into%20a%20state-owned%20asset%20and%20ensuring%20the%20proper%20management%20and%20preservation%20of%20the%20archives.%20But%20that%20would%20cost%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20%E2%80%94%20and%20thanks%20to%20the%20Duchess%2C%20the%20government%20already%20has%20a%20role%20in%20the%20foundation's%20administration%2C%20providing%20resources%20and%20guidance.%20And%20so%20the%20feud%20rages%20on%2C%20with%20the%20children%20clinging%20to%20the%20legacy%20their%20mother%20never%20wanted%20them%20to%20have.%20Leoncio%20and%20Liliane%20continue%20to%20live%20in%20separate%20wings%20of%20the%20palace%2C%20each%20imprisoned%20by%20the%20limbo%20to%20which%20Spanish%20law%2C%20and%20their%20intertwined%20fate%2C%20have%20condemned%20them.%20Gabriel%20remains%20consumed%20by%20his%20vendetta%20against%20their%20mother%2C%20and%20Pilar%20remains%20locked%20in%20battle%20with%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20family.%20The%20Duchess%2C%20with%20her%20relentless%20dedication%20to%20the%20archive%20and%20her%20disregard%20for%20her%20own%20children%2C%20left%20them%20with%20an%20acrimonious%20and%20bitter%20future.%20They%20had%20succeeded%20at%20gaining%20part%20ownership%20of%20her%20estate.%20But%20what%20they'd%20won%20seems%20more%20like%20a%20share%20in%20her%20disdain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMatthew%20Bremner%20is%20a%20writer%20based%20in%20Spain.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspanish-aristocrats-fighting-over-family-priceless-inheritance-red-duchess-estate-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734253442000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F674dcb4de45a68623a27624c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspanish-aristocrats-fighting-over-family-priceless-inheritance-red-duchess-estate-2024-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22An%20imprisoned%20duchess%2C%20a%20palace%20showdown%2C%20and%20a%20death-bed%20wedding%3A%20inside%20the%20bitter%20battle%20over%20a%20priceless%20historical%20treasure.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Matthew%20Bremner)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A31%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspanish-aristocrats-fighting-over-family-priceless-inheritance-red-duchess-estate-2024-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22AAP%20Replies%20To%20BJP's%20Dare%3A%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%2C%20Atishi%20To%20Fight%20Current%20Seats%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EArvind%20Kejriwal%20will%20contest%20the%20upcoming%20Delhi%20Assembly%20election%20from%20his%20current%20constituency%20New%20Delhi%2C%20the%20fourth%20and%20last%20list%20of%20candid